## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The core issue: RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You must **inject** context into message headers on publish and **extract** it on consume.

### Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Define a shared ActivitySource for your messaging
public static readonly ActivitySource MessagingSource = new("MyApp.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = MessagingSource.StartActivity("order.publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject the current trace context into message headers
if (activity?.Context is ActivityContext ctx)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = $"00-{ctx.TraceId}-{ctx.SpanId}-{(ctx.TraceFlags.HasFlag(ActivityTraceFlags.Recorded) ? "01" : "00")}";
    if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(activity.TraceStateString))
        props.Headers["tracestate"] = activity.TraceStateString;
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

### Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
// When consuming:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;
ActivityContext parentContext = default;

if (headers != null
    && headers.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw)
    && raw is byte[] bytes)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(bytes);
    if (ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, traceState: null, out var parsed))
        parentContext = parsed;
}

// Start a new activity linked to the producer's context
using var activity = MessagingSource.StartActivity(
    "order.consume",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext  // ← this is the key link
);

// Process the message — all downstream spans now share the same TraceId
```

### Wire it up in `Program.cs` (both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("MyApp.Messaging")   // must match the ActivitySource name
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

### Why this works

| Step | What happens |
|---|---|
| **Inject** | Producer serializes `TraceId + SpanId` into the `traceparent` header per the W3C spec |
| **Extract** | Consumer parses it back into an `ActivityContext` |
| **Link** | Passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity` makes the consumer span a **child** of the producer span — same `TraceId`, so your backend (Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP) stitches them into one trace |

### If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus

Both already do this automatically via their OpenTelemetry integrations — just enable the source:

```csharp
// MassTransit
.AddSource("MassTransit")

// NServiceBus
.AddSource("NServiceBus.*")
```

If you're on raw `RabbitMQ.Client`, the manual inject/extract above is the standard approach.
